transcripts.text: Wall Street is tapping the brakes on its record rally this week as markets worldwide take a pause on Friday.  The Dow fell 179 points, or 0.57%.  The S&P 500 dropped nearly 12 points, or 0.3%.  The Nasdaq gained 12 points, or 0.09%.  So mention the tech-heavy.  Nasdaq hit another record high today.  Housing data was strong.  More details on that in just a moment.  And factory activity reached nearly its highest level in 14 years.
